.TH "ipa_hardware_dcd_config" 9 "ipa_hardware_dcd_config" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ipa_hardware_dcd_config \- Enable dynamic clock division on IPA
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ipa_hardware_dcd_config
.BI "(struct ipa *ipa "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ipa" 12
IPA pointer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Configures when the IPA signals it is idle to the global clock
controller, which can respond by scalling down the clock to
save power.
